This paper deals with the integration of pedestrian intent estimation into an autonomous vehicle's decision-making process, as well as the development of an online monitoring framework to ensure safe interactions between the vehicle and pedestrians. This involves techniques from robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG).
